**Refining the Builder**

I'm currently focused on the `Builder.tsx` component and how I can improve the user experience and visual appeal, taking inspiration from Linktree. I'm aiming to make several enhancements to the "Builder" feature.


**Prioritizing Builder Updates**

I'm now prioritizing the Builder enhancements. Specifically, I'm focusing on the Settings and Content tabs. I'll integrate favicon uploading in Settings. In the Content tab, I'm implementing drag-and-drop link reordering and a section for social media links with icons. Customization options like font size and color are also being added. Avatar uploading is also now a feature. I will focus on CSS animations to mimic the requested feel.


**Clarifying Task Requirements**

I'm now clarifying the prompt's requirements for `Builder.tsx`. The initial "build this but same design" phrasing is misleading. After review, it specifies several distinct tasks. I need to prioritize implementing a drag-and-drop sortable list, ideally using HTML5 drag and drop, and adding a social media section and link customization options within the Content tab. Data structure updates are underway to accommodate these new features.


**Implementing File Uploads**

I'm now integrating favicon and avatar uploading. I'm using `FileReader` to manage base64 data URLs for frontend storage. I will make the offline indicator more prominent, and incorporate some entry animations into the preview blocks.

```typescript
interface LinkItem {
  id: string;
  label: string;
  url: string;
  // New fields
  style?: {
    fontSize?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
    color?: string; // Hex code or standard class
    animation?: 'none' | 'pulse' | 'bounce';
  };
}

interface SocialLink {
  id: string;
  platform: 'twitter' | 'instagram' | 'linkedin' | 'github' | 'youtube' | 'email';
  url: string;
}

interface SiteData {
  // ... existing
  avatarImage?: string; // Base64
  favicon?: string; // Base64
  socials: SocialLink[];
  links: LinkItem[];
  // ...
}
```

I'm starting to refactor the SiteData interface.
I will use standard onDragStart, onDragOver, onDrop events on the list.


**Implementing Drag-and-Drop**

I'm working on the drag-and-drop implementation for link reordering, using HTML5's drag and drop API. I'm using `onDragStart`, `onDragOver`, and `onDrop` events. I'm also preparing for image uploads, specifically for avatars and favicons, using `<input type="file">`. I will generate the base64 data URLs for frontend storage. I have added several new icons for the Socials feature. I'm sticking with CSS transitions for animations. I am modifying the SiteData interface.


**Assembling the Builder**

I'm now focusing on assembling the `Builder.tsx` component, integrating the drag-and-drop link reordering, the social media links section, and image upload components. I've written a drag-and-drop function and will integrate it into the component. I am thinking of using `<input type="file">`. I also need to make sure the previous changes, requested in XML, are included in the navbar, footer, and pricing components. I need to make sure the SiteData interface properly reflects any changes.


**Adding Link Animations**

I'm now focusing on adding smooth entry animations, inspired by Linktree, to the links in the preview. I'll implement a `stagger` effect using CSS transitions within `Builder.tsx`. I am also now getting started on the implementation. I'll need to carefully manage file uploads using the `<input type="file">` element.

